circumstances: Joseph Wheeler was reported missing from Leargan, Leven. His mother, Louise Wheeler, was concerned after Joseph failed to return home. It was believed Joseph had gone camping, a hobby he frequently enjoyed to unwind. The local police were notified and quickly began their search, contacting Joseph’s brother who mentioned that Joseph liked to visit a regular bar on Abbey Road, Newburgh. Meanwhile, Joseph's friend recalled that Joseph had spoken about setting up camp near 15 Woodside Avenue, Rosyth. After several hours of searching, the police traced Joseph to an address at 10-16 Wood Place, Rosyth, where he was found safe.
